nsldap.name: nsldap
nsldap.contactinfo: Frank Chen Postal: Netscape Communications Corp 501 East Middlefield Rd Mountain View, CA 94043 Tel: (415) 937 - 3703 Fax: (415) 937 - 4164 E-mail: frank@netscape.com
nsldap.description: An implementation of the MADMAN mib for monitoring LDAP/CLDAP and X.500 directories described in internet draft: draft-ietf-madman-ds-mib-103.txt used for iPlanet Directory Server 5

dsOpsTable.name: dsOpsTable
dsOpsTable.description: The table holding information related to the DS operations.

dsOpsEntry.name: dsOpsEntry
dsOpsEntry.description: Entry containing operations related statistics for a DS.

dsAnonymousBinds.name: dsAnonymousBinds
dsAnonymousBinds.description: Number of anonymous binds to this DS from UAs since application start.

dsUnAuthBinds.name: dsUnAuthBinds
dsUnAuthBinds.description: Number of un-authenticated binds to this DS since application start.

dsSimpleAuthBinds.name: dsSimpleAuthBinds
dsSimpleAuthBinds.reference: CCITT Blue Book Fascicle VIII.8 - Rec. X.511, 1988: Section 8.1.2.1.1. and, RFC1777 Section 4.1
dsSimpleAuthBinds.description: Number of binds to this DS that were authenticated using simple authentication procedures since application start.

dsStrongAuthBinds.name: dsStrongAuthBinds
dsStrongAuthBinds.reference: CCITT Blue Book Fascicle VIII.8 - Rec. X.511, 1988: Sections 8.1.2.1.2 & 8.1.2.1.3. and, RFC1777 Section 4.1.
dsStrongAuthBinds.description: Number of binds to this DS that were authenticated using the strong authentication procedures since application start. This includes the binds that were authenticated using external authentication procedures.

dsBindSecurityErrors.name: dsBindSecurityErrors
dsBindSecurityErrors.reference: CCITT Blue Book Fascicle VIII.8 - Rec. X.511, 1988: Section 12.7.2 and, RFC1777 Section 4.
dsBindSecurityErrors.description: Number of bind operations that have been rejected by this DS due to inappropriateAuthentication or invalidCredentials.

dsInOps.name: dsInOps
dsInOps.description: Number of operations forwarded to this DS from UAs or other DSs since application start up.

dsReadOps.name: dsReadOps
dsReadOps.reference: CCITT Blue Book Fascicle VIII.8 - Rec. X.511, 1988: Section 9.1.
dsReadOps.description: Number of read operations serviced by this DS since application startup.

dsCompareOps.name: dsCompareOps
dsCompareOps.reference: CCITT Blue Book Fascicle VIII.8 - Rec. X.511, 1988: Section 9.2. and, RFC1777 section 4.8
dsCompareOps.description: Number of compare operations serviced by this DS since application startup.

dsAddEntryOps.name: dsAddEntryOps
dsAddEntryOps.reference: CCITT Blue Book Fascicle VIII.8 - Rec. X.511, 1988: Section 11.1. and, RFC1777 Section 4.5.
dsAddEntryOps.description: Number of addEntry operations serviced by this DS since application startup.

dsRemoveEntryOps.name: dsRemoveEntryOps
dsRemoveEntryOps.reference: CCITT Blue Book Fascicle VIII.8 - Rec. X.511, 1988: Section 11.2. and, RFC1777 Section 4.6.
dsRemoveEntryOps.description: Number of removeEntry operations serviced by this DS since application startup.

dsModifyEntryOps.name: dsModifyEntryOps
dsModifyEntryOps.reference: CCITT Blue Book Fascicle VIII.8 - Rec. X.511, 1988: Section 11.3. and, RFC1777 Section 4.4.
dsModifyEntryOps.description: Number of modifyEntry operations serviced by this DS since application startup.

dsModifyRDNOps.name: dsModifyRDNOps
dsModifyRDNOps.reference: CCITT Blue Book Fascicle VIII.8 - Rec. X.511, 1988: Section 11.4.and, RFC1777 Section 4.7
dsModifyRDNOps.description: Number of modifyRDN operations serviced by this DS since application startup.

dsListOps.name: dsListOps
dsListOps.reference: CCITT Blue Book Fascicle VIII.8 - Rec. X.511, 1988: Section 10.1.
dsListOps.description: Number of list operations serviced by this DS since application startup.

dsSearchOps.name: dsSearchOps
dsSearchOps.reference: CCITT Blue Book Fascicle VIII.8 - Rec. X.511, 1988: Section 10.2. and, RFC1777 Section 4.3.
dsSearchOps.description: Number of search operations- baseObject searches, oneLevel searches and wholeSubtree searches, serviced by this DS since application startup.

dsOneLevelSearchOps.name: dsOneLevelSearchOps
dsOneLevelSearchOps.reference: CCITT Blue Book Fascicle VIII.8 - Rec. X.511, 1988: Section 10.2.2.2. and, RFC1777 Section 4.3.
dsOneLevelSearchOps.description: Number of oneLevel search operations serviced by this DS since application startup.

dsWholeSubtreeSearchOps.name: dsWholeSubtreeSearchOps
dsWholeSubtreeSearchOps.reference: CCITT Blue Book Fascicle VIII.8 - Rec. X.511, 1988: Section 10.2.2.2. and, RFC1777 Section 4.3.
dsWholeSubtreeSearchOps.description: Number of wholeSubtree search operations serviced by this DS since application startup.

dsReferrals.name: dsReferrals
dsReferrals.reference: CCITT Blue Book Fascicle VIII.8 - Rec. X.511, 1988: Section 12.6.
dsReferrals.description: Number of referrals returned by this DS in response to requests for operations since application startup.

dsChainings.name: dsChainings
dsChainings.reference: CCITT Blue Book Fascicle VIII.8 - Rec. X.518, 1988: Section 14.
dsChainings.description: Number of operations forwarded by this DS to other DSs since application startup.

dsSecurityErrors.name: dsSecurityErrors
dsSecurityErrors.reference: CCITT Blue Book Fascicle VIII.8 - Rec. X.511, 1988: Section 12.7. and, RFC1777 Section 4.
dsSecurityErrors.description: Number of operations forwarded to this DS which did not meet the security requirements.

dsErrors.name: dsErrors
dsErrors.reference: CCITT Blue Book Fascicle VIII.8 - Rec. X.511, 1988: Sections 12.4, 12.5, 12.8 & 12.9. and, RFC1777 Section 4.
dsErrors.description: Number of operations that could not be serviced due to errors other than security errors, and referrals. A partially serviced operation will not be counted as an error. The errors include NameErrors, UpdateErrors, Attribute errors and ServiceErrors.

dsEntriesTable.name: dsEntriesTable
dsEntriesTable.description: The table holding information related to the entry statistics and cache performance of the DSs.

dsEntriesEntry.name: dsEntriesEntry
dsEntriesEntry.description: Entry containing statistics pertaining to entries held by a DS.

dsMasterEntries.name: dsMasterEntries
dsMasterEntries.description: Number of entries mastered in the DS.

dsCopyEntries.name: dsCopyEntries
dsCopyEntries.description: Number of entries for which systematic (slave) copies are maintained in the DS.

dsCacheEntries.name: dsCacheEntries
dsCacheEntries.description: Number of entries cached (non-systematic copies) in the DS. This will include the entries that are cached partially. The negative cache is not counted.

dsCacheHits.name: dsCacheHits
dsCacheHits.description: Number of operations that were serviced from the locally held cache since application startup.

dsSlaveHits.name: dsSlaveHits
dsSlaveHits.description: Number of operations that were serviced from the locally held object replications ( shadow entries) since application startup.

dsIntTable.name: dsIntTable
dsIntTable.description: Each row of this table contains some details related to the history of the interaction of the monitored DSs with their respective peer DSs.

dsIntEntry.name: dsIntEntry
dsIntEntry.description: Entry containing interaction details of a DS with a peer DS.

dsIntIndex.name: dsIntIndex
dsIntIndex.description: Together with applIndex it forms the unique key to identify the conceptual row which contains useful info on the (attempted) interaction between the DS (referred to by applIndex) and a peer DS.

dsName.name: dsName
dsName.description: Distinguished Name of the peer DS to which this entry pertains.

dsTimeOfCreation.name: dsTimeOfCreation
dsTimeOfCreation.description: The value of sysUpTime when this row was created. If the entry was created before the network management subsystem was initialized, this object will contain a value of zero.

dsTimeOfLastAttempt.name: dsTimeOfLastAttempt
dsTimeOfLastAttempt.description: The value of sysUpTime when the last attempt was made to contact this DS. If the last attempt was made before the network management subsystem was initialized, this object will contain a value of zero.

dsTimeOfLastSuccess.name: dsTimeOfLastSuccess
dsTimeOfLastSuccess.description: The value of sysUpTime when the last attempt made to contact this DS was successful. If there have been no successful attempts this entry will have a value of zero. If the last successful attempt was made before the network management subsystem was initialized, this object will contain a value of zero.

dsFailuresSinceLastSuccess.name: dsFailuresSinceLastSuccess
dsFailuresSinceLastSuccess.description: The number of failures since the last time an attempt to contact this DS was successful. If there has been no successful attempts, this counter will contain the number of failures since this entry was created.

dsFailures.name: dsFailures
dsFailures.description: Cumulative failures since the creation of this entry.

dsSuccesses.name: dsSuccesses
dsSuccesses.description: Cumulative successes since the creation of this entry.

dsEntityTable.name: dsEntityTable
dsEntityTable.description: This table holds general information related to an installed instance of a directory server

dsEntityEntry.name: dsEntityEntry
dsEntityEntry.description: Entry of general information about an installed instance of a directory server

dsEntityDescr.name: dsEntityDescr
dsEntityDescr.description: A general textual description of this directory server.

dsEntityVers.name: dsEntityVers
dsEntityVers.description: The version of this directory server

dsEntityOrg.name: dsEntityOrg
dsEntityOrg.description: Organization responsible for directory server at this installation

dsEntityLocation.name: dsEntityLocation
dsEntityLocation.description: Physical location of this entity (directory server). For example: hostname, building number, lab number, etc.

dsEntityContact.name: dsEntityContact
dsEntityContact.description: Contact person(s)responsible for the directory server at this installation, together with information on how to conact.

dsEntityName.name: dsEntityName
dsEntityName.description: Name assigned to this entity at the installation site

nsDirectoryServerDown.name: nsDirectoryServerDown
nsDirectoryServerDown.description: This trap is generated whenever the agent detects the directory server to be (potentially) Down.

nsDirectoryServerStart.name: nsDirectoryServerStart
nsDirectoryServerStart.description: This trap is generated whenever the agent detects the directory server to have (re)started.
